SegregatedExperience.JobDescription:
Showed that the performance of IBM WebSphere Commerce 7 was better than IBM WebSphere Commerce 6 by nearly 5 minutes in loading all the catalog information of the different Sears Holdings Corporation brands into a data warehouse in order for the organization to make an informed decision on migrating to WCS 7. 
 Completed a proof of concept to migrate all the catalog information of Craftsman brand website from a SQL database - DB2 to a NoSQL database - MongoDB.

Developed Business Analytics (BA) solutions for in the area of Insurance, Banking to IBM customers which were featured in IBM International Conferences to showcase the usability of IBM Analytics software. 
 Analyzed and completed the integration of open-source web applications in JEE with IBM BA software for new IBM customers as part of IBM Technology Adoption program so that new IBM customers could use IBM BA software with their existing systems quickly and without many transition issues or delays to their existing systems. 
 Utilized IBM SPSS Modeler for Predictive Modelling to identify high value customers for a PC manufacturer in order to target such customers for customized marketing campaigns to increase sales and revenue. 
 Integrated SPSS products with other IBM software such as Unica Interact as part of an IBM Analytics solution aimed at Banking and Insurance customers.

Worked as an analyst investigating regression test reports on the interoperability of WebSphere and MQ for each MQ Fixpack on all platforms and identified defects to improve the functionality of the products. 
 Developed enterprise applications to validate defects and showcase the existence of defects in the products which also enabled developers to fix the identified defects. 
 Reduced the testing cycle duration from to 2 weeks by automating the administration of test resources and execution of the test cases using Jython scripting. 
 Have expertise in product migrations and product installation/administration of WAS and MQ in different platforms - AIX, Solaris, Linux, Windows and Z/OS. 
 Have knowledge about WebSphere IBM HTTP Server (IHS) and configurations for security using LDAP, database connectivity, load-balancing and high-availability of WAS during testing interoperability. 
 Have administered various features of MQ such as MQSC Commands, Distributed Queue Management, MQ Clusters, SSL Configuration on WebSphere MQ, WMQ Clients. 
 Acquired technical expertise in the interoperability of the products by troubleshooting problems spanning across different operating systems and various hardware issues. 
 Conducted trainings to customers on WAS and MQ as part of IBM Technology Adoption Program to help them adopt IBM software in their projects.

ResumeParserData.DetailResume:
TITAN TECHNOLOGIES Inc.

Ghanashyam Alakke 
Email : ghanashyam.alakke@gmail.com Phone : 812-219-1720 
 
CAREER SUMMARY 
 
More than 9 years of software engineering experience in requirement analysis, system analysis, design, 
development and testing of software products as well as data analysis and data management. 
 
TECHNICAL SKILLS 
 
Languages : Java, SQL, JavaScript, Ajax, JQuery, Python, R, Pig, Perl, Shell, XML, HTML5 , CSS	  Operating Systems : Windows, Unix - AIX, Solaris, Linux , Z/OS 
Databases : Oracle DBMS , Informix, DB2 , Derby, MongoDB, SQL Server, MySQL 
Tools : IBM WebSphere Application Server (WAS) , MQ Series (MQ) , IIS, IBM WebSphere Commerce, IBM SPSS Modeler, Hadoop, VMWare 
 
EDUCATION 
 
Masters in Computer Science from Indiana University Bloomington, graduated in May 2015 
 
ACADEMIC PROJECTS 
 
Cloud Computing 	 	 	 	 		  March 2015 - May 2015 
 
Configured and setup Hadoop in a Linux based environment. 
Implemented the KMeans clustering algorithm in Pig. 
Compared the performance of Pig with Hadoop MapReduce for KMeans algorithm on a large dataset with respect to development time and performance time and found that Pig took 1/16th the development time and its performance was nearly 2 times faster than Hadoop MapReduce. 
 
Data Management 	 	 	 	 November 2014 - December 2014 
 
Took a Twitter dataset and did data processing - data storing into MongoDB by formatting and cleaning the dataset. 
Identified the origin location of each entry in the Twitter dataset and obtained the respective geocode	  by using Google Geocode API. 
Visualized the user locations in Indiana using Tableau. 
 
 
WORK EXPERIENCE 
 
Sears Holdings Corporation, Hoffman Estates, IL, USA 	July 2015 - Present 
 
As a Systems Engineer, analyze and investigate reported problems with an application that helps store associates to complete transactions in stores using iPAD devices. 
Showed that the performance of IBM WebSphere Commerce 7 was better than IBM WebSphere Commerce 6 by nearly 5 minutes in loading all the catalog information of the different Sears Holdings Corporation brands into a data warehouse in order for the organization to make an informed decision on migrating to WCS 7. 
Completed a proof of concept to migrate all the catalog information of Craftsman brand website from a SQL database - DB2 to a NoSQL database - MongoDB. 
 
 
IBM Business Analytics, Bangalore, India 	August 2011 - July 2013 
 
Developed Business Analytics (BA) solutions for 2 years in the area of Insurance, Banking to IBM customers which were featured in IBM International Conferences to showcase the usability of IBM Analytics software. 
Analyzed and completed the integration of open-source web applications in JEE with IBM BA software for new IBM customers as part of IBM Technology Adoption program so that new IBM customers could use IBM BA software with their existing systems quickly and without many transition issues or delays to their existing systems. 
Utilized IBM SPSS Modeler for Predictive Modelling to identify high value customers for a PC manufacturer in order to target such customers for customized marketing campaigns to increase sales and revenue. 
Integrated SPSS products with other IBM software such as Unica Interact as part of an IBM Analytics solution aimed at Banking and Insurance customers.  
 
IBM Software Group, Bangalore, India 	 	 	 	 	 		  August 2006 - July 2011 
 
Worked as an analyst investigating regression test reports on the interoperability of WebSphere and MQ for each MQ Fixpack on all platforms and identified defects to improve the functionality of the products. 
Developed enterprise applications to validate defects and showcase the existence of defects in the products which also enabled developers to fix the identified defects. 
Reduced the testing cycle duration from 2 months to 2 weeks by automating the administration of test resources and execution of the test cases using Jython scripting. 
Have expertise in product migrations and product installation/administration of WAS and MQ in different platforms - AIX, Solaris, Linux, Windows and Z/OS. 
Have knowledge about WebSphere IBM HTTP Server (IHS) and configurations for security using LDAP, database connectivity, load-balancing and high-availability of WAS during testing interoperability. 
Have administered various features of MQ such as MQSC Commands, Distributed Queue Management, MQ Clusters, SSL Configuration on WebSphere MQ, WMQ Clients. 
Acquired technical expertise in the interoperability of the products by troubleshooting problems spanning across different operating systems and various hardware issues. 
Conducted trainings to customers on WAS and MQ as part of IBM Technology Adoption Program to help them adopt IBM software in their projects.	  
 
IBM Global Business Services, Bangalore, India 	 	 	 		  April 2004 - August 2006  		  
As a System Engineer, developed and maintained a web-based system using HTML, Javascript, Perl, Oracle database that stored information about problem tickets for an American Telecom Client for accurate tracking and reporting purposes. 
Gathered and documented requirements and technical specifications from business users, identified code modifications, implemented code changes and tested those changes. 
Improved problem solving abilities by analyzing and providing fixes to a wide range of application related problems. 
Gained insight into the different phases of software development through hands-on experience and production support (when required) . 
Enhanced time management skills by adhering to timelines for project completion. 
 
CERTIFICATIONS 
 
Project Management Certificate for Working Professionals from Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore in May 2013. 
Certified IBM WebSphere MQ System Administrator v6 , v7 
Certified IBM WebSphere Application Server Network Deployment System Administrator v6.1 , v7

TITAN TECHNOLOGIES Inc.	  Phone : 1-888-671-6649  	www.titan-techs.com
